title: Complete and incomplete fusion reactions in 12-C+89-Y: excitation functions and recoil range measurements

excitation functions and recoil range measurements

x4freetext: Abstract.  Excitation functions and recoil range
distributions for radioactive products formed in the
reactions of 12-C on 89-Y have been measured using
catcher foil technique followed by gamma-ray
spectrometry.  The alpha emission products show higher
cross sections than that predicted for complete fusion.
Recoil range distributions of evaporation residues
indicate incomplete momentum transfer events.  Detailed
Monte Carlo simulation of the shapes of recoil range
distributions for these processes have been carried out
using PACE2 code to extract the contributions of
incomplete fusion in the individual channels.  From the
relative yields of incomplete fusion products the
excitation energy and angular momentum of the
incompletely fused composite nucleus have been deduced.
